org.apache.flex.compiler.internal.scopes

Interface IDefinitionStore

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    EmptyDefinitionStore, LargeDefinitionStore, SmallDefinitionStore1, SmallDefinitionStore2, SmallDefinitionStore4, SmallDefinitionStore8, SmallDefinitionStoreBase

    public interface IDefinitionStore
    An IDefinitionStore is used by a scope to store a collection of definitions, organized into sets of definition sthat have the same base name.

    The IDefinitionStore is completely private to the scope and is not exposed by any scope APIs.

    Since many scopes contain only a few definitions, there are multiple implementations of this interface, optimized for storing 0, 1, 2, 4, 8, and an unlimited number of definitions.

      • getCapacity

        int getCapacity()
        Gets the maximum number of definition sets that this definition store can hold.
        Returns:
        The maximum number of definition sets.

      • createLargerStore

        IDefinitionStore createLargerStore()
        Creates another definition store with a greater capacity.

        When a call to add(org.apache.flex.compiler.definitions.IDefinition)() on this store returns false (because the store has reached its capacity), call this method to create a larger store and then call add()) on it. The second add() is guaranteed to succeed.

        Returns:
        An IDefinitionStore with a greater capacity.

      • add

        boolean add(IDefinition definition)
        Adds a definition to this store.
        Parameters:
        definition - The IDefinition to add.
        Returns:
        A flag indicating whether the definition was added. It may not be possible to add the definition because some implementations of IDefinitionStore have limited storage capacity, as a memory optimization.

      • remove

        boolean remove(IDefinition definition)
        Removes a definition from this store.
        Parameters:
        definition - The IDefinition to remove.
        Returns:
        A flag indicating whether the definition was found.

      • getDefinitionSetByName

        IDefinitionSet getDefinitionSetByName(String baseName)
        Gets the set of definitions in this store that have a specified base name.

        This method is called very frequently as part of name resolution. All implementations should be fast and avoid creating temporary objects.

        Parameters:
        baseName - The base name of the definitions you want to retrieve from the store.
        Returns:
        An IDefinitionSet containing the definition with that base name, or null if there are none.

      • putDefinitionSetByName

        void putDefinitionSetByName(String baseName,
                          IDefinitionSet set)
        Puts a specified set of definitions with a specified base name into this store.

        This is only used when a project scope has to replace a definition set in its store because it has converted definition promises in the set to actual definitions.

        Parameters:
        baseName - The base name of the definitions in the set.
        set - The IDefinitionSet of definitions to put into the store.

      • getAllDefinitions

        Collection<IDefinition> getAllDefinitions()
